  "type": "PrimaryTheme",
  "number": 5008,
  "title": "conscience",
  "comment": "An innate ability to discern the difference between right and wrong, which Scripture describes as having its origin in God himself.",
  "refgroup": null,
  "children": [
    {
      "type": "SecondaryTheme",
      "number": 5009,
      "title": "conscience, nature of",
      "comment": "The faculty, given to every individual, that is capable of producing guilt, or reassurance in the case of innocence. Though never wholly reliable, the conscience is cleansed when the individual turns to God for forgiveness. It is possible for the conscience to become deadened through lack of use.",
